.obsidian/

# One-shot batch rosters (embedded rep data, per-cohort)
scripts/provision_reps_batch.sh
scripts/reset_reps_batch.sh
scripts/provision_reps_aman_*.sh
scripts/reset_reps_aman_*.sh

# Data exports under docs/ — these carry PII: rep temp-password sheets
# (docs/pilot_reps_*) and merchant lead exports with plaintext NIDs
# (docs/merchants_export_*). Distribute, then delete — never commit.
#
# Blanket by extension rather than by filename prefix: docs/ tracks prose and
# html only, so a tabular file here is always an export, never a fixture. The
# runbook's "Download CSV" flow and the export-visit-photos edge function both
# emit names we cannot predict, and a prefix match would let them through.
# A genuinely committable data file needs a deliberate `git add -f`.
docs/*.csv
docs/*.tsv
docs/*.xlsx
docs/*.xls

# Office owner-lock files (~$ prefix escapes the globs above; embed local username)
~$*
